  "text": "# Envoy Access Log Format Field Completeness Audit\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Envoy access log formatting system is implemented across multiple source files in the `source/common/formatter/` directory. The system uses a two-level command parsing approach:\n\n1. **HTTP-specific commands** registered in `HttpBuiltInCommandParser` (source/common/formatter/http_specific_formatter.cc)\n2. **Stream info commands** registered in `getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders()` (source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.cc)\n\n## Command Operator Implementation\n\n### HTTP-Specific Operators (%REQ%, %RESP%, etc.)\n\nThese are implemented in `source/common/formatter/http_specific_formatter.cc` via the `HttpBuiltInCommandParser::getKnownFormatters()` function, which registers the following command operators:\n\n- **%REQ(header-name)%** - Implemented via `RequestHeaderFormatter` class. Formats request headers with optional max length truncation.\n- **%RESP(header-name)%** - Implemented via `ResponseHeaderFormatter` class. Formats response headers.\n- **%TRAILER(header-name)%** - Implemented via `ResponseTrailerFormatter` class. Formats response trailers.\n- **%LOCAL_REPLY_BODY%** - Implemented via `LocalReplyBodyFormatter` class.\n- **%ACCESS_LOG_TYPE%** - Implemented via `AccessLogTypeFormatter` class.\n- **%GRPC_STATUS%** - Implemented via `GrpcStatusFormatter` class. Supports CAMEL_STRING, SNAKE_STRING, and NUMBER formats.\n- **%GRPC_STATUS_NUMBER%** - Shorthand for GRPC_STATUS with NUMBER format.\n- **%REQUEST_HEADERS_BYTES%** - Implemented via `HeadersByteSizeFormatter`.\n- **%RESPONSE_HEADERS_BYTES%** - Implemented via `HeadersByteSizeFormatter`.\n- **%RESPONSE_TRAILERS_BYTES%** - Implemented via `HeadersByteSizeFormatter`.\n- **%STREAM_INFO_REQ(header-name)%** - Alternative request header formatter using stream info.\n- **%TRACE_ID%** - Implemented via `TraceIDFormatter` class.\n\n### Stream Info Operators (%DURATION%, %UPSTREAM_HOST%, etc.)\n\nThese are implemented in `source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.cc` via the `getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders()` function, which returns a `StreamInfoFormatterProviderLookupTable` (flat_hash_map) containing:\n\n#### Duration-Related Operators:\n- **%REQUEST_DURATION%** - Time from first downstream RX byte to last downstream RX byte\n- **%REQUEST_TX_DURATION%** - Time from first to last upstream TX byte\n- **%RESPONSE_DURATION%** - Time from first upstream RX byte\n- **%RESPONSE_TX_DURATION%** - Duration between downstream and upstream response\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_HANDSHAKE_DURATION%** - Downstream connection handshake duration\n- **%ROUNDTRIP_DURATION%** - Complete roundtrip duration\n- **%DURATION%** - Current request duration from stream info (line 1034-1041)\n- **%COMMON_DURATION(...)%** - Configurable duration between arbitrary time points (line 1042-1046)\n- **%UPSTREAM_CONNECTION_POOL_READY_DURATION%** - Connection pool callback latency (line 1737-1756)\n\n#### Bytes-Related Operators:\n- **%BYTES_RECEIVED%** - Downstream bytes received\n- **%BYTES_SENT%** - Downstream bytes sent\n- **%BYTES_RETRANSMITTED%** - TCP retransmitted bytes\n- **%PACKETS_RETRANSMITTED%** - TCP retransmitted packets\n- **%UPSTREAM_WIRE_BYTES_RECEIVED%** - Upstream wire bytes received\n- **%UPSTREAM_HEADER_BYTES_RECEIVED%** - Upstream header bytes received\n- **%UPSTREAM_WIRE_BYTES_SENT%** - Upstream wire bytes sent\n- **%UPSTREAM_HEADER_BYTES_SENT%** - Upstream header bytes sent\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_WIRE_BYTES_RECEIVED%** - Downstream wire bytes received\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_HEADER_BYTES_RECEIVED%** - Downstream header bytes received\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_WIRE_BYTES_SENT%** - Downstream wire bytes sent\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_HEADER_BYTES_SENT%** - Downstream header bytes sent\n\n#### Upstream Host and Connection Operators:\n- **%UPSTREAM_HOST%** - Upstream host address with port (line 1084-1100, uses `StreamInfoAddressFormatterProvider`)\n- **%UPSTREAM_HOST_NAME%** - Upstream host hostname or address (line 1063-1083)\n- **%UPSTREAM_CLUSTER%** - Upstream cluster observability name (line 1114-1130)\n- **%UPSTREAM_CLUSTER_RAW%** - Upstream cluster raw name (line 1131-1146)\n- **%UPSTREAM_LOCAL_ADDRESS%** - Upstream local address with port (line 1147-1158)\n- **%UPSTREAM_LOCAL_ADDRESS_WITHOUT_PORT%** - Upstream local address without port (line 1159-1170)\n- **%UPSTREAM_LOCAL_PORT%** - Upstream local port only (line 1171-1182)\n- **%UPSTREAM_REMOTE_ADDRESS%** - Upstream remote address with port (line 1183-1191)\n- **%UPSTREAM_REMOTE_ADDRESS_WITHOUT_PORT%** - Upstream remote address without port (line 1192-1200)\n- **%UPSTREAM_REMOTE_PORT%** - Upstream remote port only (line 1201-1209)\n- **%UPSTREAM_CONNECTION_ID%** - Upstream connection ID (line 1101-1113)\n- **%UPSTREAM_REQUEST_ATTEMPT_COUNT%** - Number of upstream request attempts (line 1210-1217)\n\n#### Protocol and Response Code Operators:\n- **%PROTOCOL%** - Request protocol (HTTP/1.1, HTTP/2, etc.)\n- **%UPSTREAM_PROTOCOL%** - Upstream protocol\n- **%RESPONSE_CODE%** - HTTP response status code\n- **%RESPONSE_CODE_DETAILS%** - Response code details string\n- **%CONNECTION_TERMINATION_DETAILS%** - Connection termination details\n- **%RESPONSE_FLAGS%** - Response flags in short format\n- **%RESPONSE_FLAGS_LONG%** - Response flags in long format\n\n#### Address Operators (Downstream):\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_LOCAL_ADDRESS%** - Downstream local address with port\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_LOCAL_ADDRESS_WITHOUT_PORT%** - Downstream local address without port\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_LOCAL_PORT%** - Downstream local port only\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_REMOTE_ADDRESS%** - Downstream remote address with port\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_REMOTE_ADDRESS_WITHOUT_PORT%** - Downstream remote address without port\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_REMOTE_PORT%** - Downstream remote port only\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_DIRECT_REMOTE_ADDRESS%** - Downstream direct remote address (before proxying)\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_DIRECT_REMOTE_ADDRESS_WITHOUT_PORT%** - Without port\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_DIRECT_REMOTE_PORT%** - Just the port\n\n#### SSL/TLS Operators:\n- **%UPSTREAM_TLS_CIPHER%** - Upstream TLS cipher suite\n- **%UPSTREAM_TLS_VERSION%** - Upstream TLS version\n- **%UPSTREAM_TLS_SESSION_ID%** - Upstream TLS session ID\n- **%UPSTREAM_PEER_ISSUER%** - Upstream peer certificate issuer\n- **%UPSTREAM_PEER_CERT%** - Upstream peer certificate (PEM encoded)\n- **%UPSTREAM_PEER_SUBJECT%** - Upstream peer certificate subject\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_TLS_CIPHER%** - Downstream TLS cipher suite\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_TLS_VERSION%** - Downstream TLS version\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_TLS_SESSION_ID%** - Downstream TLS session ID\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_ISSUER%** - Downstream peer certificate issuer\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_CERT%** - Downstream peer certificate\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_SUBJECT%** - Downstream peer certificate subject\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_FINGERPRINT_256%** - SHA256 fingerprint of peer cert\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_FINGERPRINT_1%** - SHA1 fingerprint of peer cert\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_SERIAL%** - Peer certificate serial number\n- **%UPSTREAM_PEER_URI_SAN%** - URI SAN from upstream peer cert\n- **%UPSTREAM_PEER_DNS_SAN%** - DNS SAN from upstream peer cert\n- **%UPSTREAM_PEER_IP_SAN%** - IP SAN from upstream peer cert\n- **%UPSTREAM_LOCAL_URI_SAN%** - URI SAN from upstream local cert\n- **%UPSTREAM_LOCAL_DNS_SAN%** - DNS SAN from upstream local cert\n- **%UPSTREAM_LOCAL_IP_SAN%** - IP SAN from upstream local cert\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_URI_SAN%** - URI SAN from downstream peer cert\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_DNS_SAN%** - DNS SAN from downstream peer cert\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_IP_SAN%** - IP SAN from downstream peer cert\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_LOCAL_URI_SAN%** - URI SAN from downstream local cert\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_LOCAL_DNS_SAN%** - DNS SAN from downstream local cert\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_LOCAL_IP_SAN%** - IP SAN from downstream local cert\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_CERT_V_START%** - Downstream peer cert validity start time\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_PEER_CERT_V_END%** - Downstream peer cert validity end time\n- **%UPSTREAM_PEER_CERT_V_START%** - Upstream peer cert validity start time\n- **%UPSTREAM_PEER_CERT_V_END%** - Upstream peer cert validity end time\n\n#### Time and Routing Operators:\n- **%START_TIME(format)%** - Request start time in specified format\n- **%EMIT_TIME(format)%** - Log emission time in specified format\n- **%REQUESTED_SERVER_NAME%** - SNI value from TLS ClientHello\n- **%ROUTE_NAME%** - Name of matched route\n- **%CONNECTION_ID%** - Downstream connection ID\n\n#### Metadata Operators:\n- **%DYNAMIC_METADATA(namespace:key:...)%** - Dynamic metadata from filters\n- **%CLUSTER_METADATA(namespace:key:...)%** - Upstream cluster metadata\n- **%UPSTREAM_METADATA(namespace:key:...)%** - Upstream host metadata\n\n#### Filter State and Environment:\n- **%FILTER_STATE(key)%** - Downstream filter state\n- **%UPSTREAM_FILTER_STATE(key)%** - Upstream filter state\n- **%ENVIRONMENT(var-name)%** - Environment variable value\n\n#### Other Operators:\n- **%HOSTNAME%** - Local hostname\n- **%FILTER_CHAIN_NAME%** - Name of the matched filter chain\n- **%VIRTUAL_CLUSTER_NAME%** - Name of the matched virtual cluster\n- **%TLS_JA3_FINGERPRINT%** - JA3 TLS fingerprint\n- **%UNIQUE_ID%** - Random UUID\n- **%STREAM_ID%** - Stream ID from provider\n- **%DOWNSTREAM_TRANSPORT_FAILURE_REASON%** - Transport failure reason\n- **%UPSTREAM_TRANSPORT_FAILURE_REASON%** - Upstream transport failure reason\n\n## Parser Flow\n\n### Command Resolution Chain (substitution_formatter.h:86-112):\n\n1. **SubstitutionFormatParser::parse()** - Main entry point that tokenizes the format string and identifies %command% patterns.\n\n2. **BuiltInCommandParsersBase<FormatterContext>::commandParsers()** - Returns registered built-in parsers.\n   - For HTTP context: Returns `HttpBuiltInCommandParser`\n\n3. **HttpBuiltInCommandParser::parse()** - Attempts to parse HTTP-specific commands (REQ, RESP, TRAILER, etc.)\n   - Uses `getKnownFormatters()` lookup table at line 330-420\n   - Returns nullptr if command not found, allowing fallback to next parser\n\n4. **User-provided command parsers** - Custom formatters can be registered\n\n5. **StreamInfoFormatterBase** (fallback) - Used for all remaining commands\n   - Calls `getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders()` at line 821\n   - Returns `StreamInfoDurationFormatterProvider`, `StreamInfoStringFormatterProvider`, `StreamInfoAddressFormatterProvider`, etc.\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Helper Classes (stream_info_formatter.cc:600-750):\n\n- **StreamInfoStringFormatterProvider** (line 601-617) - Formats string fields from StreamInfo\n- **StreamInfoDurationFormatterProvider** (line 620-655) - Formats duration/nanoseconds as milliseconds\n- **StreamInfoUInt64FormatterProvider** (line 658-674) - Formats uint64 integer fields\n- **StreamInfoAddressFormatterProvider** (line 677-750) - Formats network addresses with three extraction modes:\n  - `withPort()` - Address with port\n  - `withoutPort()` - Address without port\n  - `justPort()` - Port number only\n\n### Registration Mechanism\n\nAll command operators are registered in two lookup tables:\n1. **HttpBuiltInCommandParser::getKnownFormatters()** (http_specific_formatter.cc:330-420) - HTTP-specific commands\n2. **getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders()** (stream_info_formatter.cc:821-1757) - Stream info commands\n\nEach entry maps a command name to:\n- CommandSyntaxChecker flags (COMMAND_ONLY, PARAMS_REQUIRED, PARAMS_OPTIONAL, LENGTH_ALLOWED)\n- A lambda function that creates the appropriate FormatterProvider instance\n\n## Integration Point\n\nThe formatter registration is registered globally via macro at http_specific_formatter.cc:443:\n```cpp\nREGISTER_BUILT_IN_COMMAND_PARSER(HttpFormatterContext, HttpBuiltInCommandParser);\n```\n\nThis allows the parser to be discovered and registered when formatting contexts are instantiated.\n"
